d in other forms that require captcha.\n\nYou can roll your own function by calling assets/components/captcha/captcha.php where you want the image\nand then comparing the user\'s input to the $_SESSION[\'veriword\'] variable.\n\nSee the code in the core/components/captcha/captcha.plugin.php file.\n\";s:9:\"changelog\";s:1428:\"Changelog for Captcha.\n\nCaptcha 3.3.4-pl\n----------------\nFix critical bug in v. 3.3.3\n\nCaptcha 3.3.2-pl\n----------------\nDocumentation corrections\nUpdate Copyrights\n\nCaptcha 3.3.1-pl\n----------------\nUpdate for MODX 2.3\n\nCaptcha 3.3.1-pl\n----------------\nMore reliable uninstall\nAdded NL translation\nFix bug with plugin remaining in cache after uninstall\nRemove Captcha System Settings on uninstall\n\nCaptcha 3.3.0-pl\n----------------\nFixed bug with session var not being written\n    (fixes intermittent Captcha failure - Thanks to Garry Nutting!)\nAdded German Lexicon files\nMinor bug fixes\n\nCaptcha 3.2.5\n-------------\nAdded Spanish language files\n\nCaptcha 3.2.4\n-------------\nFixed bug with failed validator\n\nCaptcha 3.2.3\n-------------\nFixed bug in Transport Package\n\nCaptcha 3.2.2\n-------------\nUpdated PhpDoc comments\nAdded changelog.txt\nAdded readme.md\nReorganized for Git\nRevolution Transport Package updated\nConverted tabs to spaces\n\nCaptcha 3.2.1\n-------------\nTest for Necessary GD and FreeType functions on install\n\nCaptcha 3.1.0\n-------------\nUpdated for Revolution RC3\nFixed bug with captcha words\nConverted $modx->config calls to getOption()\n\nCaptcha 3.0.3\n-------------\nFixed bugs in build script\nMoved target directory\nAdded license and readme\n\n Captcha 3.0.2\n -------------\n$_SESSION mathstring value can override system setting\nUpdates to build script\n\n Captcha 3.0.1\n -------------\nFirst Revolution release\n\n\n\";s:13:\"setup-options\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"signature\";s:16:\"captcha-3.3.4-pl\";s:6:\"action\";s:26:\"workspace/packages/install\";s:8:\"register\";s:3:\"mgr\";s:5:\"to